        <ArticleTitle>Propofol-related hepatotoxicity: a systematic review.</ArticleTitle>
        <Abstract>
          <AbstractText Label="BACKGROUND" NlmCategory="BACKGROUND">Propofol is widely used for anesthesia induction.</AbstractText>
          <AbstractText Label="METHODS" NlmCategory="METHODS">We searched PubMed and Embase for relevant studies.</AbstractText>
          <AbstractText Label="RESULTS" NlmCategory="RESULTS">A total of 23 studies met inclusion criteria.</AbstractText>
          <AbstractText Label="CONCLUSIONS" NlmCategory="CONCLUSIONS">Propofol hepatotoxicity is rare but clinically significant.</AbstractText>
        </Abstract>
